    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Which one of the following statements is true about the small signal voltage gain of a MOSFET based single stage amplifier?\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Common source and common gate amplifiers are both inverting amplifiers\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "Common source and common gate amplifiers are both non-inverting amplifiers\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Common source amplifier is inverting and common gate amplifier is non-inverting amplifier\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Common source amplifiers is non-inverting and common gate amplifier is inverting amplifier"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\n  <thead>\n\n    <tr>\n\n      <th>Parameters</th>\n\n      <th>Common Source (CS)</th>\n\n      <th>Common Drain (CD)</th>\n\n      <th>Common Gate (CG)</th>\n\n    </tr>\n\n  </thead>\n\n  <tbody>\n\n    <tr>\n\n      <td><strong>Input resistance</strong></td>\n\n      <td>$R_{i} = \\infty$</td>\n\n      <td>$R_{i} = \\infty$</td>\n\n      <td>$R_{i} = \\frac{1}{g_{m}}$</td>\n\n    </tr>\n\n    <tr>\n\n      <td><strong>Output resistance</strong></td>\n\n      <td>$R_{0} = R_{0} \\parallel R_{L}$</td>\n\n      <td>$R_{0} = \\dfrac{1}{g_{m}}$</td>\n\n      <td>$R_{0} = R_{0} \\parallel R_{L}$</td>\n\n    </tr>\n\n    <tr>\n\n      <td><strong>Voltage gain</strong></td>\n\n      <td>\n\n        $           A_{v} = -\\,g_{m}\\,R'_{L}           \\quad\\bigl(R'_{L} = R_{L} \\parallel R_{D}\\bigr)         $\n\n      </td>\n\n      <td>\n\n        $           A_{v} \\;=\\; \\frac{g_{m}\\,R'_{L}}{1 + g_{m}\\,R'_{L}}           \\;\\approx\\; 1         $\n\n      </td>\n\n      <td>\n\n        $           A_{v} = g_{m}\\,R'_{L}           \\quad\\bigl(R'_{L} = R_{L} \\parallel R_{D}\\bigr)         $\n\n      </td>\n\n    </tr>\n\n    <tr>\n\n      <td><strong>Phase shift</strong></td>\n\n      <td>$180^\\circ$</td>\n\n      <td>$0^\\circ$</td>\n\n      <td>$0^\\circ$</td>\n\n    </tr>\n\n  </tbody>\n\n</table>\n<p>From the above table.</p>\n<p>(i) In common source amplifier the phase shift between input and output voltage is $180^{\\circ}$. Hence, it is an inverting amplifier.</p>\n<p>(ii) In common drain amplifier the phase shift between input and output voltage is $0^0$. Hence, it is a non inverting amplifier.</p>\n<p>(iii) In common gate amplifier the phase shift between input and output voltage is $0^{\\circ}$. Thus, it is a non inverting amplifier.</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
